-- New Raiffeisen Bank Int'l shares priced at 28.50 eur 
-- By Michael Shields
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 09:25AM EST
-- None



VIENNA, Jan 22 (Reuters) - Raiffeisen Bank International <RBIV.VI> placed 97.5 million shares in a capital increase at 28.50 euros each, valuing the deal at 2.78 billion euros ($3.77 billion), the Austrian bank said on Wednesday.

The stock was trading at 29.88 euros by 1424 GMT, slightly down from Tuesday's close at 29.90, after the placement to institutional investors in an accelerated bookbuilding process. A rights issue for existing shareholders at the same price follows. They will be entitled to one new share for each two existing shares they hold.